1. Best Case (Ω - Big Omega)
The best case is the absolute ideal scenario. It represents the minimum number of steps the algorithm needs to take. We use the mathematical symbol Ω (Omega) to denote it.
Example: Searching for a specific card in a shuffled deck.
The Scenario: The very first card you flip over happens to be the exact card you were looking for.
Time Complexity: O(1) (Constant time).
